    <section class="info">
        <div class="info-box">
            
            <h3>Habitat</h3>
            <p>Geckos are found in warm regions across the world, including rainforests, deserts, and grasslands. They are known for their adaptability and ability to thrive in various environments.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>Behaviors</h3>
            <p>Geckos are primarily nocturnal creatures, using their excellent vision to hunt at night. They have specialized toe pads that allow them to climb walls and even walk upside down.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>Diet</h3>
            <p>Most geckos are insectivores, feeding on a variety of insects like crickets and mealworms. Some species also eat fruits and nectar.</p>
        </div>
